message:
Fulfill this database query: give me all products that cost more than 50.  Use these TABLE_DEFINITIONS to satisfy the database query.

TABLE_DEFINITIONS

CREATE TABLE product_categories (
product_category_id integer,
product_id integer,
category_id integer
);

CREATE TABLE suppliers (
supplier_id integer,
supplier_name text,
contact_number text,
email text,
address text
);

CREATE TABLE supplier_products (
supplier_product_id integer,
supplier_id integer,
product_id integer,
unit_price numeric,
available_quantity integer
);

CREATE TABLE products (
product_id integer,
product_name text,
category_id integer,
price numeric,
stock_quantity integer
);

CREATE TABLE supplier_ratings (
rating_id integer,
supplier_id integer,
user_id integer,
rating integer,
comments text
);

CREATE TABLE products (
product_id integer,
product_name text,
category_id integer,
price numeric,
stock_quantity integer
);

Based on the provided table definitions, the SQL query to get all products that cost more than 50 would be:

```sql
SELECT *
FROM products
WHERE price > 50;
```

Please execute this query and let me know if you need any further assistance.
